AI Middleware Policy v1

Status

Accepted

⸻

Purpose

This document defines the middleware layer rules for all AI execution paths, including:
	•	AI assistants
	•	automation agents (e.g. OpenClaw / workflow bots)
	•	internal AI tools
	•	LINE / Email / API-based AI integrations

The middleware exists to:
	•	enforce org-scoped data access
	•	prevent prompt injection escalation
	•	route all AI data access through controlled interfaces
	•	ensure consistency with AI data boundary policy

⸻

Core Principle

Middleware does not grant access.
Middleware enforces access.

All data safety must already be guaranteed at the database layer.
Middleware must strictly respect and enforce, never bypass.

⸻

Architecture Overview

User / Agent / External Input
        ↓
AI Middleware
        ↓
AI-safe RPC / AI-safe Views
        ↓
Database (org-scoped, fail-closed)
