## Minimal Implementation Scope (v1)

This version intentionally limits scope:

### Included
- org context enforcement
- RPC routing control
- fail-closed behavior
- injection resistance at access level

### Deferred (Phase 2+)
- AI conversation guardrails (style / tone)
- advanced anomaly detection
- cross-request behavior tracking
- rate limiting
- audit logs for AI decisions

---

## Anti-Patterns (Forbidden)

### 1. Middleware bypassing DB safety
❌ calling base tables directly

### 2. Service role leakage
❌ using elevated credentials in AI runtime

### 3. Prompt-driven scope
❌ "User asked for all shipments, so allow it"

### 4. Silent fallback
❌ returning partial data when org resolution fails

### 5. AI self-routing
❌ allowing AI to decide which RPC to call without restriction

---

## Example Execution Flow

```text
User: "Show me recent shipments"

Middleware:
- inject org_id
- validate request
- call ai_list_shipments_v1(limit=10)

DB:
- enforce org_id filter

Result:
- only org-scoped shipments returned
``` id="ai-mw-flow"

---

## Summary

Middleware is the enforcement layer that ensures:

- AI cannot escape org boundaries
- AI cannot escalate privileges via prompt
- AI always operates within approved data channels

The database enforces safety.  
Middleware ensures it is always used correctly.

Together, they form a complete AI security boundary.
:::
